<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I think that Abashi:

1) Has an impossible job.

2) Tries very hard to do said job.

3) Often dismisses people's carefully thought out issues too easily.

4) Fails to demand accountability and improvement on behalf of players for continued inexcusably shoddy quality assurance (i.e. testing of changes or existing features) by Verant.

5) Has developed the acute tunnel vision that comes from being too close to a situation for too long.

I don't think it's fair to criticize without advancing a solution, so here's mine. Abashi's job needs to be handled by a staff of people, say 10 or so to begin with, who are responsible for accounting for each and every thread on Whineplay. New threads would accumulate in a shared queue from which the mini-Abashis would take ownership of them on a first-come, first-served basis, then categorize them. Some threads are incoherent, whiny, or offensive, and should be categorized under "No Response". Some have already been answered and could be categorized under "FAQ", perhaps resulting in an auto-reply to the thread indicating that the answer can be found by reviewing the FAQ.  The rest would comprise the "Response Required" threads. It would be the responsibility of these individuals to communicate with the appropriate parties, to test the issue themselves when possible, to formulate a truly responsive reply taking into account both the player's perspective and Verant's original intention or worldview related to the matter at hand, and finally to update the FAQ with their conclusions to allow future inquiries along the same lines to be referred there.

Hey, I can dream...

